$ Git: template directory
@ template directory

The content of the *template directory* is copied by the command `→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/init` to the
→ development/version-control-systems/git/_git[Git directory/repository].

The location of the template directory is determined with the following order (the first one found is accepted):
  • Cmmand line option `--template=<dir>` of `→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/init`
  • `$GIT_TEMPLATE_DIR` → development/environment-variable[environment variable]
  • `init.templateDir` → development/version-control-systems/git/options[option]
  • Default template directory under `→ Linux/fhs/usr/share[/usr/share/git-core/templates` (Windows: `<git-install-root>\mingw64\share\git-core\templates`).
